title: Sunny queer home in Prospect Lefferts Gardens
posting_body: ['Looking for two folks to sign onto a year-long lease for a quiet, sunny home in Prospect Lefferts Gardens.', "It's a 3BR/2Bath - with two rooms available - an upstairs room with a shared bathroom ($1000), and a basement room with a private living room and bathroom ($1400).", 'We are 5-6 blocks from the park, off the Sterling 5 & 2.', 'Backyard, rooftop access, washer/dryer in-unit & a dishwasher.', 'I like to find the balance between occasionally hanging out as roommates, occasionally having friends over outside, but mostly keeping a quiet home.', 'Not a party house.', 'I keep things clean but am mostly a live and let live kind of gal.', 'The one thing to note is that this apartment had fruit flies in the past and they come back if dishes are left out, so being diligent about dishes is a must.', 'A few other notes:', '-No pets.', '-Rooms and common areas will come unfurnished.', '-Move-in date is 10/1, and rental application is due to the landlord 8/15.', '-Would rent the two upstairs rooms to a couple for $2200.', 'Queer folks to the front, or queer-friendly folks also welcome :)', 'A little about me - I like a quiet space that feels like a home space, and love living with community-minded, social justice-minded folks.', 'I love plants and growing things and being outside.', 'I am trying to start a queer camping crew and am in a queer book club :) I’m a fan of biking, hiking, doing yoga, and am a total bookworm.', 'I am outgoing and friendly but not a big party person.', 'I’m still fairly COVID-conscious because of new variants and am looking for folks who are the same.', 'I work from home one day a week - but I am looking for new jobs so that might shift.', 'I prefer to live with folks who work outside of the home at least some of the time.']

posting_body: ['While rents are going up everywhere in the NYC metro area, this rent is about 3k less than what you find in the metro area and a great location and safe location as well.', ' No shootings, muggings, assaults in this hood..', 'Safe walk to metro north..', 'By Owner..2 bedroom/1bath apt for rent.', 'fresh paint.', '2nd floor.', '10 min walk to metro north station in woodlawn, 20 min commute to grand central station.', 'Heat and water included.', '$ 2200 per month.', '1st, last, security and references.', 'accommodates 3 personas', 'Huge eat in kitchen, tall ceilings, extra storage areas, wood floors.', 'Street parking', 'TO QUALIFY FOR THIS APARTMENT FOLLOW THE 30% RENT RULE...', 'In simple terms, the 30% rule recommends that your monthly rent payment not be more than 30% of your gross monthly income.', '...', 'That would leave 70% of your gross monthly income to cover other necessities, such as utilities and food, discretionary spending, debt repayment, and savings.', 'Rule of Thumb: How Much Should You Spend on Rent? -', 'The <URL> › ... › Real Estate Resources', 'Search for: 30% rent rule', 'HOW MUCH DO I HAVE TO EARN IN ORDER TO AFFORD  $2200 A MONTH IN RENT..', 'You may have heard of the general rule of thumb here, which is that 30% of your monthly income should go to rent.', "If you make $7800 a month at your job, that's $1950 that you can afford to spend in housing costs.", '(Another way to calculate this is to take your entire yearly income and divide it by 40.)Feb 8, 2019', 'How Much Rent Can You Afford? - <URL> › tips › how-much-rent-can-you...', '2200 a month..its a no brainier..', 'Call business # 10AM -5 PM   # 914 776 9139, lv msg if no one answers.........(THIS MEANS NO E-MAILS!!-BECAUSE YOU WILL BE WASTING YOUR TIME...why you ask?', 'BECAUSE THIS AD IS POSTED AS A SERVICE TO THE OWNER OF THIS PROPERTY.', 'THE PERSON WHO POSTED THIS DOES NOT OWN THE PROPERTY!!!!)']

posting_body: ['PRIVATE DECK!', '- Large and luxury 2 bedroom / 2 baths!', '- Welcome to Fulton Crossing!', 'A new luxury apartment complex located in Brooklyn’s beautiful Bedford-Stuyvesant.', 'An up-and-coming neighborhood in the heart of New York City’s most charming borough, it boasts tree-lined streets, stunning architecture, enchanting parks, and a diverse yet welcoming atmosphere – all within close proximity to the city’s bustling urban hubs.', 'This luxury Brooklyn apartment building offers large studio, 1 bedroom, 2 bedroom and 3 bedroom apartments in Bed-Stuy that feature unobstructed city views, spacious layouts, and state-of-the-art amenities.', 'If you’re searching for a Bedford-Stuyvesant apartment, Fulton Crossing is ready to welcome you home.', 'Building includes two elevators, a furnished rooftop with grills and amazing Manhattan views, gym, Lounge/Co-working area, kids play room, shared courtyard, laundry rooms and parking.', 'Great location half block away from Kingston & Throop C Local train and 2 blocks away from Nostrand Avenue A Express train.', 'A minute away from grocery stores and the bars/restaurants in Bed-Stuy and Crown Heights.', 'Apartment features modern open-concept designs.', 'Sleek finishes and modern hardware add an contemporary edge, while large French-paned windows perfectly frame beautiful views of Bed-Stuy and of natural light.', 'Kitchen with stainless steel appliances, including dishwasher, and extra space for table/island.', 'Spacious bathrooms, large closet, split AC units, hardwood floors throughout, and video intercom system!', 'Text Leo: 917-808-0442']

title: Houseboat Dream year round
posting_body: ['32 FOOT CONVERTED CARVER HOUSEBOAT ---TURNKEY FULLY FURNISHED COMPLETE WITH DISHES, POTS, PANS, KITCHEN APPLIANCES, LINENS, TOWELS, TV, AND EVERYTHING ELSE YOU NEED TO LIVE IMMEDIATELY.', 'Safe, private keyed entrance marina in Mill Basin, Brooklyn in protected harbor on Jamaica Bay one minute from Express Bus to Manhattan and Bus to Q train.', 'Also one minute to supermarket, dry cleaner, drugstore, and many restaurants.', 'The average rent in Brooklyn is $3,000 a month.', 'When you include first, last and Brokers fee, that could add up to over $10,000 just to move in.', 'The Marina fee paid each season amounts to just $480 a month and you purchase the Houseboat for $15,000.', '(Please no inquiries as to only renting)', 'I refit the carver many years ago and raised my daughter on it.', 'It has two Delonghi SAFE wall heaters, 20 gallon electric hot water heater, air conditioner, TV, full bathroom with electric toilet, sink, and glass stall shower, 100 volt and 12 volt electrical, 120 gallon fresh water tank,  a wetbar with a working sink and liquor cabinet, several closets, a dinette table that lowers into a double bunk, a private standup forward berth with closet, drawers for clothing, and a door, plenty of storage, full kithchen with a 3 burner Princess electric stove top, blender, George Forman grill, silverware, cups, plates, glasses pots, pans, utensils etc., a Hamilton Beach Rotisserie oven, fridge with freezer, and an upper deck with a canopy to enjoy the sunset.', 'It has its own electric meter.', 'The boat has been specially insulated for winter living.', 'It is available immediately if need be.', 'I look forward to hearing from you, Michael']

title: Ultra-spacious, Renovated 1 Bedroom Starter Apartment
posting_body: ['PROPERTY INFO', 'Rent: $2,200 / Month', 'Beds: 1', 'Bath: 1', 'Available Date: 08/06/2022', "If you didn't already know East Harlem is a trendy spot, now you do.", 'And apartments like this are why.', 'A renovated, roomy true 1 bedroom, with separate kitchen, stainless steel appliances, tiled bath, hardwood floors, situated in the back of the a well-maintained building for maximum tranquility and privacy.', 'Text, email or call Gesha-Marie for viewing or virtual tour.', '6462397412.Known for its murals, East Harlem is a street art shrine.', "Surrounded by an eclectic selection of eateries and bars, it's 12 min walk to Central Park, and just 25 minutes to Midtown from the 6 train, 103rd Street.", "- Stainless Steel Appliances- Hardwood Floors- Tiled BathEast Harlem's (El Barrio or Spanish Harlem, if you prefer) vibrant roots are depicted through its large-scale murals, discussed in its museums, and revered by its members.", 'Plenty of wonderful bistros, wine bars, and Latin establishments dot the streets.', 'East River Plaza gives you easy access to Costco and Target.', 'Central Park to the west and Marcus Garvey Park to the east offer plenty of green space to relax.', 'The draw of its deep-seated traditions is matched by superb subway and public transportation accessibility.']

closet.', 'Call/text Howard:914-843-8556', 'Testimonial:', 'After aimlessly searching for an apartment in Stanford Connecticut, I was fortunate enough to connect with Howard.', 'I told him a bit about the type of apartment I was looking for, and expected to have a standard apartment viewing experience.', 'My experience was anything but standard.', 'It took just one short conversation and Howard was able to pick up on the nuances of my personal and professional needs.', 'He curated a short list of buildings to visit and apartments to view.', "Howard's selections were so spot on,  I had a difficult time choosing which I loved most.", 'On the day I arrived in Stamford, Howard picked me up from the train station and gave me a tour of the city.', 'He pointed out where I could purchase groceries and other necessities, and gave me a thorough tour of the downtown area (where I now live).', "My experience working with Howard was, hands-down, the most pleasant experience I've had apartment hunting.", 'Howard was not only knowledgeable and personable, I truly felt he was always looking out for my best interest.', '10/10.', 'In a post pandemic world,  flooded by Ida, places to live were very far and few between.', 'I was struggling to find anything and working with multiple agents.', 'Right when I was about to give up I found Howard!!!', ' Now this goes without saying but if you are blessed enough to find someone like him be truly thankful and grateful.', ' Howard met me one day for a viewing….which did not pan out.', ' Instead of giving up he instantly got in his phone and continued to follow-up with his network.', ' We spent 3 hours together viewing numerous apartments until we found one that worked!', ' He stayed with me through the entire process to ensure I was taken care of not even leaving while I was filling the paperwork and offering the help me move in when the time came.', ' Now this goes without saying, but in a world where simple human kindness is scarce Howard has it in spades makes you feel like you are part of his family.', ' I would highly recommend Howard to anyone for literally anything but if you need a new home or apartment he is the person to go too!', ' Thank you from the bottom of my heart.', 'RB']

title: Gorgeous 3 bedroom, 2 bath
posting_body: ['SHOWINGS BY APPOINTMENT ONLY; MASKS REQUIRED (COVID PRECAUTION):', 'Friday 7/29: 12pm-2pm', 'Sunday 7/31: 2:30pm-6pm', 'Beautiful and recently renovated 3 bedroom, 2 bathroom apartment in Riverdale, available June 1.', 'A two-minute walk to Key Food, Walgreens, Starbucks and shopping on Johnson Avenue, five-minute walk to Riverdale Avenue shops, and a ten-minute walk to the 1 train.', "Walking in is a marble staircase and it's one flight up to the open dining room.", 'Straight ahead is the kitchen with cherry cabinets, granite countertops, and stainless steel appliances.', 'Behind the kitchen is a bedroom and the main floor bathroom.', 'Through the dining room, a large living room, with a door to a patio.', 'Off the living room is a small bedroom, and to your right are the stairs to the 700 sq ft+ master suite.', 'In the master suite is an en-suite bathroom with double vanities and a jacuzzi tub.', 'With more than 15 windows, this is an extremely sunny apartment.', 'In-unit laundry is in the basement (2 washers and 2 dryers).', 'Laundry area is shared with the live-in super.', 'Access to the backyard and grill.', 'Small gatherings that end by 10pm are allowed - simply coordinate with the other tenants.', 'Included in the rent are heat and hot water.', 'Tenant pays electric and gas (approximately $60-$250 monthly, depending on your air conditioner use).', 'Parking available, off-street, $150/month additional.', 'The apartment is pet friendly (up to 2 well-behaved pets considered), and strictly non-smoking.', 'Perfect for commute to Columbia and Upper West Side, about a 45-minute train ride to midtown.', 'Income 40x the monthly rent with good credit.', 'Guarantors accepted.', '1-year and 2-year leases offered.', 'Please email with any questions and to schedule a viewing.', 'Thanks!']

title: New, beautifully furnished, parking, balcony, stunning views
neighborhood: Greenwood Heights close to Park Slope
posting_body: ['This brand new, beautifully furnished 1BR with balcony delivers stunning views from midtown to downtown Manhattan to the New York Harbor and Brooklyn including the Empire State Building, the World Trade Center and the Statue of Liberty.', 'A quiet, peaceful setting to watch the sunsets and birds, work at the standing desk, workout on the SoulCycle bike, or go for a stroll in Prospect Park.', 'Bright and airy with full floor to ceiling windows throughout that provide outstanding natural light all day long and 180 degree views.', 'The apartment has hardwood floors, central heat and AC, Bosch dishwasher, KitchenAid refrigerator and gas range, LG washer/dryer, SoulCycle bike and shower with deep soaking tub.', 'Fully equipped kitchen, dining table, sofa and chairs, standing desk, 55” TV, bookshelves, and queen size Casper bed.', 'Rooftop deck with 360 degree views of the city.', 'Elevator, bike room, package room.', 'Looking for someone respectful who will treat the apartment as their own.', 'SoulCycle cycling & Equinox workouts subscription included.', 'No pets, no parties, no smoking.', 'Apartment is available for 1 year or more.', 'Parking spot in covered garage available for additional fee.', 'This boutique 6 floor building is located in Greenwood Heights, a vibrant and charming neighborhood and a short walk to groceries, amazing restaurants, bars, and coffee shops.', 'Short walk to Park Slope, convenient and direct transportation to Midtown Manhattan, Wall Street, Williamsburg, Long Island City and more.', '2 blocks to Subway.', 'Prospect Park, Industry City, Barclay’s Center, the Brooklyn Museum and the Brooklyn Botanical Garden are all within easy reach.']

posting_body: ['SEE BELOW FOR PAYMENT SAVINGS OPTIONS.', 'For rent: 2 bedroom,1 bath basement apartment.', 'Excellent condition, ceramic tile throughout.', 'Brand new refrigerator.', '1 full size bedroom, and also one smaller bedroom which is perfect for an office/childs room.', 'Close to SUNY stony brook, 8 minutes away.', 'Close to all stores.', 'Located in Centereach.', 'Driveway parking, Separate entrance.', 'Quiet location. includes all utilities and wifi.', '1 months rent +1 month security.', 'No Smoking/No pets.', 'Ideal for SBU student.', 'Available August 1st 2022.', 'THE FOLLOWING RENTAL PAYMENT OPTIONS ARE AVAILABLE:', 'OPTION A)—-If you pay a lump sum for a year in advance, the rent drops to $1500/month.', '(Save $250/month) ($18,000 upfront plus 1 month security=$19,500)', 'OPTION B)—If you pay a lump sum for 6 months rent in advance, the rent is $1750 per month.', '(This means $10,500 due upfront for 6 months, plus 1 month security= $11,200.', 'Please note that with this option, the next 6 months in advance will be due upfront at the conclusion of the first 6 months)', 'OPTION C)--If you pay on a Monthly basis--the rent is $1950 with 2 months security required.', 'With this option, great or excellent credit is required as well as references and proof of income.', 'No exceptions.', 'Priority will be given to applicants choosing option', 'A', 'ALSO--- please answer the following questions and provide your contact number with your email.', 'Emails without this information will NOT receive a reply.', '1) Who would the apartment be for?', '2) Any pets?', '3) Any smoking?', '4) When are you looking to move?', '5) Which rental option (A or B, or c) are you interested in?', 'Thank you']

title: Enormous 3 bedroom top shelf Bruce Wayne style located in Yorkville!
posting_body: ['The Frame Building’ – Downtown lofts, Uptown living.', 'Newly renovated full-floor residence located on prime East 80th Street centered between Central Park & Carl Schurz Park on the Upper East Side.', 'This stunning 1,640 sq.', 'ft. apartment features two bedrooms, three full bathrooms, a home office and a private 44 SF balcony; it blends the character of a quintessential pre-war loft with the best in modern upgrades and luxury condo finishes.', 'The keyed elevator opens into a bright, beautifully proportioned space with 5” oak hardwood floors, soaring ceilings of 10ft and a 19ft x 26ft 6in wide living and dining room with large south-facing windows overlooking E80th Street.', 'A sleek open kitchen features white lacquered Leitch cabinetry with abundant storage, under-cabinet lighting, white Quartz countertops and premium appliances, including a Fisher & Paykel fridge, oven, and gas range.', 'The quiet bedrooms face north overlooking adjacent townhouse gardens; the well-proportioned King suite has a custom-built walk-in closet and ensuite white Cararra marble bathroom with double vanity.', 'A generous home office offers the option to add a pressurized wall for a third room if needed.', 'White Quartz window sills throughout.', 'This exceptional apartment benefits from an oversized Blomberg washing machine and externally vented dryer, central air system, recessed lighting, sound minimizing construction methods, and windows on 3 exposures allowing for optimal natural light throughout.', 'Constructed in 1915 and steeped in history, this classic 6-story pre-war elevator building on the Upper East Side was occupied by the world-renowned Framing and Restoration company ‘Lowy’ for several decades.', 'Founded in 1907, Lowy amassed the world’s largest collection of antique frames and has been appointed to work with the world’s most prized art collections for clients such as the Metropolitan Museum of Art and The White House.', 'Completed reimagined and converted in 2018, 223 E80th St is now comprised of 5 full-floor luxury rental apartments with a private residential entrance at street level, secure Virtual doorman intercom system, and fob-keyed elevator access to each floor.', 'Amenities include a landscaped & furnished common roof terrace, lobby delivery closet, bicycle racks, and dedicated private storage room for every apartment in the basement level.', 'Perfectly situated mid-block on tree-lined E80th St, the building offers close proximity to Uptown’s best dining, shopping, fitness, gourmet groceries, as well as excellent transportation including the 4, 5, 6, and Q trains.', 'Pet friendly on a case-by-case basis.', 'Heat and Hot water is included.', 'Video tour is available upon request', 'Contact 347-858-3929']

posting_body: ['PLEASE SEE BELOW FOR PAYMENT SAVINGS OPTIONS.', 'IF AD IS STILL POSTED--THE APARTMENT IS STILL AVAILABLE.', 'For rent: 2 bedroom,1 bath basement apartment.', 'Excellent condition, ceramic tile throughout.', 'Brand new refrigerator.', '1 full size bedroom, and also one smaller bedroom which is perfect for an office/childs room.', 'Close to SUNY stony brook, 8 minutes away.', 'Close to all stores.', 'Located in Centereach.', 'Driveway parking, Separate entrance.', 'Quiet location. includes all utilities and wifi.', '1 months rent +1 month security.', 'No Smoking/No pets.', 'Ideal for SBU student.', 'Available August 15th 2022.', 'THE FOLLOWING RENTAL PAYMENT OPTIONS ARE AVAILABLE.', 'THE PRICE OF RENT IS AS FOLLOWS:', 'OPTION A)—-If you pay a lump sum for a year in advance, the rent drops to $1500/month.', '(Save $450/month) ($18,000 upfront plus 1 month security=$19,500).', 'You will also receive one FREE month of rent.', ' So you would be paying for 12 months and then receive one free month.', ' This is a savings of $4500.', 'OPTION B)—If you pay a lump sum for 6 months rent in advance, the rent is $1750 per month.', '( Save $200/month)', 'This means $10,500 due upfront for 6 months, plus 1 month security= $11,200.', 'Please note that with this option, the next 6 months in advance will be due upfront at the conclusion of the first 6 months)', 'OPTION C)--If you pay on a Monthly basis--the rent is $1950 with 2 months security required.', 'With this option, great or excellent credit is required as well as references and proof of income.', 'No exceptions.', 'Priority will be given to applicants choosing option', 'A', 'ALSO--- please answer the following questions with your email and phone number.', ' Emails without this information will NOT receive a reply.', '1) Who would the apartment be for?', '2) Any pets?', '3) Any smoking?', '4) When are you looking to move?', '5) Which rental option (A or B, or C) are you interested in?', 'Thank you']

title: ***New Listing: S.S. Kitchen, Queen Size BDRM, ELV BLDG, Doorman
posting_body: ['Amazing Corner 1 Bedroom, 1 Bath with a pass-through windowed kitchen, stainless steel appliances, floor-to-ceiling windows, an in-home washer/dryer, spacious closets, and northwestern exposure.', 'The Upper East Side apartments at One Carnegie Hill have it all!', "Live in this neighborhood and you'll discover the many attractions that make the Upper East Side so charming and chic.", "Whether you're in the mood to catch a movie, see an exhibit, bike in Central Park or meet a friend for an espresso, there's always something to do when you live on the Upper East Side.", 'Michael K - Listing ID: 838X274', 'One Carnegie Hill fits comfortably into a neighborhood characterized by the most luxurious Manhattan residences.', "The main area of One Carnegie Hill's lobby, designed by Rockwell Group, is defined by a barrel-vaulted ceiling that evokes the elegant lobbies of these classic Upper East Side apartments.", 'Amenities include:', '-On-premises pet spa,', "-Children's playroom", '-Health and fitness lounge and club,', '-Indoor swimming pool,', '-Lush rooftop sun terrace.', 'This apartment was initially listed at $4,650.', 'The lease you would be taking over includes approval for two pets ($75/pet) and TWO memberships to the in-building gym ($80/person), meaning the total monthly rent should be $4,960.', 'Negotiated down to $4,600!!!', 'Lease Assignment remainder 7 months.', 'Move out Date: FEB 28th, 2023, with option to renew with management.', 'Message me for more details!', 'To view this apartment today, please contact:', 'Michael', '323-864-4374', 'Adam', '516-673-7939', "Additionally, I have plenty of units available in Murray Hill, Midtown East , Hell's Kitchen, Gramercy, Upper West Side etc.", 'Including doorman and brownstone buildings with outdoor space, patios, balconies, laundry and more.', "If this isn't your ideal place, let me know", "and I'm certain I can find it!"]

posting_body: ['Balcony apartment!', '- Welcome to Fulton Crossing!', 'A new luxury apartment complex located in Brooklyn’s beautiful Bedford-Stuyvesant.', 'An up-and-coming neighborhood in the heart of New York City’s most charming borough, it boasts tree-lined streets, stunning architecture, enchanting parks, and a diverse yet welcoming atmosphere – all within close proximity to the city’s bustling urban hubs.', 'This luxury Brooklyn apartment building offers large studio, 1 bedroom, 2 bedroom and 3 bedroom apartments in Bed-Stuy that feature unobstructed city views, spacious layouts, and state-of-the-art amenities.', 'If you’re searching for a Bedford-Stuyvesant apartment, Fulton Crossing is ready to welcome you home.', 'Building includes two elevators, a furnished rooftop with grills and amazing Manhattan views, gym, Lounge/Co-working area, kids play room, shared courtyard, laundry rooms and parking.', 'Great location half block away from Kingston & Throop C Local train and 2 blocks away from Nostrand Avenue A Express train.', 'A minute away from grocery stores and the bars/restaurants in Bed-Stuy and Crown Heights.', 'Apartment features modern open-concept designs.', 'Sleek finishes and modern hardware add an contemporary edge, while large French-paned windows perfectly frame beautiful views of Bed-Stuy and of natural light.', 'Kitchen with stainless steel appliances, including dishwasher, and extra space for table/island.', 'Spacious bathrooms, large closet, split AC units, hardwood floors throughout, and video intercom system!', 'Text Leo: 917-808-0442']

title: HUMONGOUS==HIGH CEILING==GREAT LIGHTING==OAK WOOD FLOORS==TOP FLOOR==
posting_body: ['Luxury building in the Financial District, you walk into this beautifully renovated apartment.', 'Upon immediately entering the large foyer, you will notice the large California-style closet providing an efficient storage solution for the apartment.', 'Adjacent to it is the brand new, large pass-thru gourmet kitchen, equipped with granite counters, custom cabinetry, stainless steel GE appliances (including a dishwasher, refrigerator, stove top, microwave, and ventilation system).Slightly further up is the full bathroom boasting a marble-tile finish and a large vanity mirror.', 'The large living space is an effortless FLEX-2 conversion, very comfortably.', 'With substantial remaining space for a living quarters, you can decide where to situate any accommodating furniture (couch, coffee table, etc).', 'Large over-sized windows on the Eastern exposure flood the hardwood floors with natural light and provide fascinating views of the Brooklyn Bridge, South St Seaport, and surrounding waterscape.', 'Settled on Water St, you are surrounded by an endless amount of options in terms of fine dining, shopping, culture and activities.', 'South St Seaport is across the street from your doorsteps.', '55 Fulton Market is conveniently located one block to the North.', 'Titanic Memorial Park is across the street.', "NYC's historic Financial District and all its attractions are a five minute walk to the South-West.", 'Transit options surround the area, with the primary hub being the newly renovated Fulton Street Station (operational 24 hours a day) where you can catch eight different train lines (including 2, 3, 4, 5, A, C, J, Z).']

posting_body: ['SUN AND LIGHT', 'TREETOP VIEWS', 'CORNER UNIT', 'SOUTHERN EXPOSURE', 'BIG WINDOWS', 'LARGE ROOMS', 'THROUGH WALL A/C IN UNIT', 'LAUNDRY IN BUILDING', 'WINDOWED GYM', 'LARGE SHARED COURTYARD', 'ELEVATOR', 'BIKE STORAGE', 'PETS WELCOME', '12% BROKER FEE', 'TEXT 516.262.3693 TO SCHEDULE AN IN PERSON OR VIRTUAL SHOWING.', "DON'T WAIT, WON'T LAST.", 'VIDEO OF SIMILIAR UNIT WITH SAME SQUARE FOOTAGE HERE:', 'https://youtu.be/2-l5jFL73jc', 'Hi everyone, we have a great size corner 1 bedroom, available Aug 15.', 'Spacious living area and bedroom, awesome new kitchen with dishwasher, large closets and large bathroom.', 'Easily work from home here, great for couples.', 'Modern and clean.', 'Laundry in building, plus large shared courtyard, bike storage, gym, elevator, and package room round out this deal nicely.', 'Beautiful lobby, extremely secure building, nice street and area.', 'The apartment is located on Houston Street off Avenue C', 'right near many popular spots – Poco, Pardon My French, Eastpoint, Niagara, The Wayland, Summit Bar, Supper, Lil Frankies, Nublu - the heart of Alphabet City’s buzzy food and bar scene.', 'Huge supermarket less than 5 minute walk, 24 hour Duane Reade on the corner, endless great food and drink options throughout the entire neighborhood, free Olympic size outdoor city pool and beautiful Tompkins Square Park is only a 5 minute walk away.', 'The F, J, M, and Z trains at either 2nd', 'Ave Station or Essex Station are an easy >10 minute walk and the L train on 14th Street and Avenue A is close as well.', 'The M9 bus goes all the way from Kips Bay to FIDI /Battery Park City, the M21 crosstown bus that goes down Houston is right around the corner, the M14D bus which runs crosstown across 14th street is a block away and there is a Citibike station 2 blocks away as well.', 'This is a residential NYC neighborhood with tons of supermarkets, drycleaners, hardware stores, take-out spots, 24 hr bodegas, etc.', 'Easy walking distance to the Lower East Side, Union Square, Soho, Nolita, Little Italy, etc.', 'Small, friendly east village landlord requires 1 month rent and 1 month security and out of town guarantors are accepted if needed.', 'One year lease minimum, no short term.', 'We are a long-time local realtor specializing in the areas we know and love best, happy to assist our clients through difficult markets.', 'The landlord requires that we ask prospective tenants a few questions before showing the unit, text 516.262.3693 for immediate response, otherwise if you need to email please add a US contact number.', 'Thank you!', 'Cheers,', 'Nick and Pam', '516.262.3693', 'WE HAVE MULTIPLE LISTINGS FOR 1, 2, 3, AND 4 BEDROOMS THROUGHOUT THE EAST VILLAGE, WEST VILLAGE, LES, SOHO, NOLITA, KIPS BAY, GRAMERCY, CHELSEA AND UNION SQUARE AREA.', 'CALL US TODAY AND WE’LL BE HAPPY TO ASSIST IN YOUR SEARCH.', 'ALSO CHECK OUT NICK’S BLOG FOR THE BEST OF EATING AND DRINKING IN THE EAST VILLAGE!', '<URL>/']

great kitchen with lots of cabinets, granit countertop, recessed lightes and breakfast nook, kitchen leads to a unique dining room with an entrance to a huge very private backyard.', 'At the lower level, there is another 1100 sq ft harwood floor space which includes: 4+ rooms, restroom, walk-in bath, private street entrance, and access to the private backyard.', 'This space is ideal for someone who started their business from home or needs a quiet space for different family members to study, play, relax, or have their live-in nany close by.', 'Every room has a water connection if needed.', 'You will have access to the backyard from both levels.', 'The entire rent can be written off in tax deductions if the lower level used as an office.', 'Located at a prominent professional Bay Ridge community, in a business oriented area with plenty of restaurants, shopping, banks, medical offices in every building, 2 minutes from the R train subway station and extensive Brooklyn bus routes, five minutes from the X27 and X37 Express buses to Manhattan, and a 10 minute walk to the 69th Street Ferry to Manhattan.', 'Retired medical professionals are offering for rent this wonderful duplex where you will have place for everything: family and entertaining, and start or expand your own business.', 'Central A/C and heater combination extraquiet split system allows for temperature control in every room.', 'Laundry unit is at the lower level.', 'Parking space provides 2 car parking opprtunity.', 'Rent 8,500/month for both office and living quaters.', 'At least 2-year lease.', 'EMAIL to schedule viewing.', 'No pets please.', 'No smoking please.']

title: 4 Bedrooms + Office W/ Hardwood-Like Floors, Private Yard
posting_body: ['This is a 4 Bedroom + Office in the Union City area of New Jersey.', 'The Apartment Features Hardwood-Like Floors, Private Yard, Professional Grade Stainless Steel Stove, FIOS, and Tile Backsplash.', 'Pets accepted on approval.', 'NO BROKER FEE FOR IMMEDIATE START', 'Kitchen - Dining Room 15 x 10', 'Living Room 16.5 x 9', 'First Bedroom 13 x 11', 'Second Bedroom 9.5 x 7', 'Third Bedroom 11 x 9', 'Fourth Bedroom 12 x 9', 'Office 12.5 x 4', 'Yard 39.5 x 22', 'Listing ID#7893', 'Orientation in Relation to Other Neighborhoods', 'North of Jersey City & Hoboken', 'South of West New York, North Bergen & Guttenberg', 'East of Secaucus', 'West of Weehawken', 'Near Houses of Worship, Shopping and Local Dining Establishments on Bergenline and New York Aves.', '20 Minutes to Midtown via Public Transit or Car!', 'The soul of the city can be found along Bergenline Avenue, a bustling commercial strip where many of the area s residents come to shop, dine and meet up with old friends.', 'Just across John Fitzgerald Kennedy Boulevard, in North Bergen, another mall offers big-box stores, an LA Fitness gym, a ShopRite and a multiplex movie theater, while the many restaurants of Hoboken and Jersey City are within walking distance or a short cab or jitney ride away.', 'Despite its compact size, Union City boasts a number of parks, three with water features, including Firefighter s Memorial Park on Palisade Avenue, which has an Olympic-size pool.', 'Washington Park, where the city borders Jersey City Heights, has a dog run, tennis and basketball courts and baseball fields.', 'The NJ Transit 123 buses make five stops in Union City, with travel times of between 10 and 30 minutes to the Port Authority in New York.', 'Other options include traveling to Hoboken or Jersey City to catch the PATH train; taking an eight-minute ferry from Weehawken to 39th Street; or taking a seven-minute ferry from Hoboken to Wall Street.', "For travel to Jersey City and New York, many residents rely on the jitney buses that run along several of Union City's north-south arteries."]

title: Central Ridgefield Studio for Rent!
posting_body: ['Hi, we’re Gus and Courtney!', 'We live in Ridgefield with our cat, Nutmeg.', 'We have a studio apartment available to rent right near Main Street in Ridgefield.', 'Want the full scoop?', 'Read on to find out more:', 'About the Apartment:', 'The apartment is located above a detached garage.', 'We used to live in the house toward the front of the property, but we’ve since moved (only 10 minutes away) and it’s now a rental.', 'The property’s right in the thick of things, within easy walking distance to downtown restaurants, walking trails, the Ridgefield Playhouse, and shops.', "It's a studio apartment but has a loft that can accommodate a queen-sized mattress (or storage).", 'The rest of the space is open, though a butcherblock countertop separates the kitchen and living areas.', 'Almost one entire wall is window, so the space gets wonderful light.', ' Between this and the lofted ceiling, the apartment feels roomy.', "There's a full bath and, while small, an efficient kitchen with a propane gas stove/oven.", 'We recently completed several renovations, including:', '•\tA custom iron ladder & railing for loft access', '•\tNewly painted walls', '•\tNew title: *** NEW 1 BED, 1 BA, PRIVATE PATIO, DISHWAHER unit in NOLITA, NYC!
posting_body: ['This newly renovated one bedroom is perfect.', 'The living space is great for entertaining guests.', 'The kitchen has an abundance of counter space, custom-finished cabinets, and beautiful appliances.', 'The bedroom can comfortably fit a queen sized bed, dresser, and more.', 'The bathroom also has been recently renovated, with brand new fixtures and vanity, while having a beautiful marble tiling throughout.', "Originally part of Little Italy, this neighborhood North of today's Little Italy has transformed into an upscale, coveted area of the city to call home.", "Nolita's brick and cast iron buildings are historic, defining the famous architecture the area is known for.", 'The streets are lined with restaurants and boutiques that bring tinges of Old New York to mind, and while comparisons have been made between Nolita and Soho, Nolita is maturing into a distinct neighborhood in its own right.', 'The cobblestone streets provide a quaint feel rarely experienced in New York City, yet its location ensures easy access to busy, high-quality restaurants and stores.', 'Nolita is not as commercial as the rest of Manhattan, making it an ideal living environment for someone looking for a trendy and convenient location without the constant bustle of Manhattan.']
